ways of assessing

00:30:57.910 --> 00:31:01.660
current public opinion,
identifying sectors of support,

00:31:01.660 --> 00:31:04.670
identifying the means
of communication,

00:31:04.670 --> 00:31:09.260
and messages to effectively
influence public opinion.

00:31:09.260 --> 00:31:11.230
That public opinion
and expectation

00:31:11.230 --> 00:31:14.050
guarantees that a Supreme
Court ruling is implemented.

00:31:14.050 --> 00:31:16.420
Or that a new law holds weight.

00:31:16.420 --> 00:31:18.550
That becomes one of
those primary bulwarks

00:31:18.550 --> 00:31:21.100
against the
assumption of impunity

00:31:21.100 --> 00:31:22.990
that powerful groups
in the countries

00:31:22.990 --> 00:31:24.310
can do whatever they want.

00:31:24.310 --> 00:31:27.490
Because if they believe that the
citizenry will confront them,

00:31:27.490 --> 00:31:29.350
they'll think twice.

00:31:29.350 --> 00:31:31.210
NGOs, human rights
NGOs, it's like were

00:31:31.210 --> 00:31:35.020
